  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the train in between never stopped for any other reason but for a day-- or a-- for a-- for a 1/2 an hour or 3/4 of an hour, somewhere in an unknown-- or not even on a station, just on the tracks.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We had no-- second day went by.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then finally, on the third day, we were deep in Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We knew we are in Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And during all this time, we had no such a thing as nobody cared, if we have water, food, anything.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But naturally, I mean, I don't have to tell you that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because it's-- it's-- it's still coming from the-- still coming from a-- from the ghetto that every single family had what to eat, something to eat, or something to-- to munch on, or something to-- to keep you alive.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And finally, the third day-- memory wise, the third day in the morning-- 'cause it's either the morning, noon time-- the train came in a screeching halt.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And now something, what I would like to bring to-- I don't know if the proper time or place to tell you, that it was-- on the train there was a conversation between dad and another gentleman.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And his closest friend was a-- was our family doctor and his closest friend.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And that is unbelievable, that during that-- that time when it was quite obvious that every single effort required and needed for the war effort, that so many SS guard were able to guard us.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And so many train, a huge, big train was ever able to carry us instead of carrying some kind of material to the front.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
